<p>
  <span class="nym">Avice</span>
  <span class="gen">f.</span>
  
  <span class="etym"><span class="lang">Latin</span> <i>avitia</i> 'birds; the bird family', or possibly <span class="lang">Old German</span> <i>Aveza</i>.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>This name was rare outside of England.</p>
<p>The English form <i>Auis</i> is witnessed in 1379 in the relational byname <i>Auissoñ</i> (<span class="bibl"><span class="key">WRYPT1</span> <span class="loc">p. 166</span></span>).</p>
  
  


